        "commentary": "Cisco F3Q26 beat is meaningful — $15.8B revenue +12% YoY is the strongest top-line growth in years, signaling AI infrastructure orders finally converting to revenue. Splunk integration accretive, but the real tell is enterprise networking re-acceleration. AI orders from webscale ($1B+ run-rate guided earlier) now landing in P&L. Read-through bullish for **ANET** (competitive read on Ethernet-for-AI), **JNPR** (HPE deal close pending), and silicon suppliers **AVGO** / **MRVL** (Tomahawk/Jericho switching ASICs ship into Cisco boxes). Optical names **CIEN** / **COHR** benefit from datacenter interconnect pull-through. Watch for ANET reaction — if Cisco won share in Ethernet AI fabric, ANET premium compresses. Sector tailwind for networking; mild headwind for legacy SDN/security pure-plays that Cisco bundles against. EPS +10% < revenue +12% suggests margin pressure from Splunk amortization — monitor mix.",
